description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wintle Ward is a 16 bed, Female Adult Acute Mental Health ward covering the Oxford City area. Our in-patient areas are AIMS accredited and we are rated Good by the CQC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Band 6 Charge Nurse supports the Ward Manager and Modern Matron in improvement and innovation work and leading the Multidisciplinary team. As a Band 6 you will have a key role in supporting staff to provide high quality patient care. It is one of the most challenging and important roles on the ward and is a combination of clinical, leadership and managerial skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Why come and work for us?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We believe in-patient services is an expert area of mental health&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We work hard to always improve our services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We believe that we can make a real difference to our patients and their loved ones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are dynamic and forward thinking in our approach to patient care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from enthusiastic, dedicated and hardworking individuals. In return we can offer you: a friendly and supportive working environment, regular case management, Individual and group clinical supervision, on-going training and personal development There is scope to develop management and clinical skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Harkirtan Tanday, Ward Manager Wintle Ward. 01865 902481 Harkirtan.Tanday@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tony Walmsley, Modern Matron Wintle Ward. 01865 902481 tony.walmsley@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
